OL,3,CCommunity 'absolutely thrilled' after
OL,4,Cstolen altar cross returned 30 years on
OL,6,F"Maybe there's been a bit of
OL,7,Fconscience or maybe it was a relative
OL,8,Fwho was involved and felt it was
OL,9,Fimportant to give it back to the
OL,10,Fchurch and their conscience got the
OL,11,Fbetter of them.
OL,13,F"Maybe they decided the best way to do
OL,14,Fthat was to leave it for Elmore
OL,15,Fbecause they knew that Elmore was the
OL,16,Fverger and leave it anonymously
OL,17,Foutside his door."
OL,19,FElmore Crump, in his 80s, cleaned the
OL,20,Fcross and now Tufnell believes it
OL,21,Flooks "tremendous."
